      • expandConfiguration

        public com.cyc.session.CycSessionConfiguration expandConfiguration(com.cyc.session.CycSessionConfiguration config,
                                                          com.cyc.session.EnvironmentConfiguration environment)
                                                            throws com.cyc.session.exception.SessionConfigurationException
        Recurses over CycSessionConfiguration if it specifies another configuration. CycSessionConfigurations can specify other CycSessionConfigurations. For example, an EnvironmentConfiguration could specify to load a configuration from a particular properties file, which in turn says to interactively prompt the user for configuration data. Typically you wouldn't want to chain beyond two levels -- an environmental configuration specifying another configuration method -- but there are cases where you might, and this allows that flexibility. Order of precedence:
        • If the CycSessionConfiguration is sufficiently configured, use it.
        • Load a configuration file, if specified.
        • Use a SessionConfigurationLoader, if one is specified.
        • Poll the user interactively via a GUI prompt, if allowed and if in a graphical environment.
        • Otherwise, return the original (presumably insufficient) configuration to be dealt with somehow.
        Parameters:
        config -
        environment -
        Returns:
        the configuration
        Throws:
        com.cyc.session.exception.SessionConfigurationException
